    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>AIRLINE MERGER TALKS EXTENDED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British Airways and KLM Royal Dutch Airlines extend exclusivity period of their merger negotiations (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Two major European airlines -- British Airways and KLM Royal Dutch Airlines -- have extended the exclusivity period of their merger negotiations. ''The parties recognize that a business rationale for a potential merger exists,'' the companies said. KLM says it is planning to file a formal merger proposal with the European Union by the end of September.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
